.TH "from_kuid" 9 "from_kuid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
from_kuid \- Create a uid from a kuid user-namespace pair.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "uid_t" from_kuid
.BI "(struct user_namespace *targ "  ","
.BI "kuid_t kuid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "targ" 12
The user namespace we want a uid in.
.IP "kuid" 12
The kernel internal uid to start with.

Map \fIkuid\fP into the user-namespace specified by \fItarg\fP and
return the resulting uid.

There is always a mapping into the initial user_namespace.

If \fIkuid\fP has no mapping in \fItarg\fP (uid_t)-1 is returned.
